Author: POWER
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: The friendly natives ... were busy ... cleaning their arms, singing `hakas', and making speeches, while waiting till the old women opened the native ovens, which, well filled with pork and kumeras, sent up an appetising steam in all directions.
Notes: 1849 Power Sketches in NZ 29 Aug 24th [1846].-

